Package: lorax
Title: Speak for the Trees
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Max", "Kuhn", , "max@posit.co", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2402-136X")),
    person("Posit Software, PBC", role = c("cph", "fnd"))
  )
Description: Provides a unified interface for extracting information from
    tree- and rule-based models. Functions include extracting logical rules
    that define terminal nodes, identifying predictors that were actually used
    in splits, retrieving variable importance scores, and converting trees to
    the 'partykit' format for visualization. Supports models from packages
    including 'rpart', 'ranger', 'randomForest', 'xgboost', 'lightgbm', 'C50',
    'Cubist', 'bart', and 'grf'.
